The paper deals with dynamic graph algorithms, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of fixed parameter tractability (FPT) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The specific problems studied in the paper (Vertex Cover, Cluster Vertex Deletion, Chromatic Number, Feedback Vertex Set) are all related to graph theory, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Finally, the use of dynamic graphs for NP-hard problems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category, which often deals with optimization problems.
